For the next week, Ashley and I are heading out of town with Jamin’s family, and honestly… it’s about time we go on another trip. This one is going to be a little chaotic, probably exhausting, but 100% worth it, because we’re going to Yosemite National Park!! I’ve been looking forward to this for weeks now, to the point where it’s been hard to think about anything else. There’s just something about getting out of town, being in the mountains, and doing something a little adventurous that I love.

I already know it’s going to be one of those trips where we’re tired the whole time but don’t even care because we’re having so much fun. Early mornings, long days, lots of exploring… all of it. Exactly my kind of trip.

Anyways, I’ll definitely keep you, dear reader, updated on all the adventures we get into while we’re there, because I already know there’s going to be a lot to tell.
In the meantime, enjoy the week and the spring showers 🤍

